cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about improving the efficiency of convolutional neural networks for visual recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new layer architecture, which involves linear channel projection, suggesting that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed method, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on image classification tasks, which could also place it under cs.MM (Multimedia).
